Joseph Olaoluwa Air Peace has announced the arrival of another aircraft, ERJ-145, which is currently undergoing C-check. The aircraft, with registration number 5N-BVD, arrived Lagos on Monday night, according to a statement titled ‘Air Peace receives another ERJ-145 from C-check’, issued by the airline on Tuesday. Spokesperson of the airline, Stanley Olisa, said, “Most of our aircraft were out on C-check during the COVID-19 pandemic, but they have started arriving one after the other.” The airline had a few weeks back received a new acquisition, taking its current Embraer 145 fleet to eight. Copyright PUNCH.
